    <subsubsection>
      <title>Domain and Range</title>
      <exercises><exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Let <m>M</m> be the function that assigns to each living human being their legal date of birth
            (month and day).
            What is the domain of <m>M</m>?
            What is the range of <m>M</m>?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            Domain is all living human beings;
            range is all possible dates (month and day)
          </p>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Let <m>p</m> be the rule that assigns to each vehicle registered in the state of New York its license plate number.
            What is the domain of <m>p</m>?
            What is the range of <m>p</m>?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
