            using a function called <m>C</m>.
            <ol marker="a">
              <li>
                <p>
                  State the input variable and quantity,
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  state the output variable and quantity, and
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  describe the relationship using both the variables and the quantities they represent using the phrasing
                  <q><em>
                  <me>
                    } is a function of \underline{
                  </me>
                  </em></q>.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Write an equation which relates the variables and the function.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <ol marker="a">
              <li>
                <p>
